text: Our data imply that inactivation of TP53/RB1 function is a possible early event in the histogenesis of synchronous and metachronous SCLC/NSCLC. Moreover, the non-adenocarcinoma (SCLC) component might arise from the adenocarcinoma (NSCLC) component through a mechanism that involves the activation of the ASCL1 and PI3K/AKT1 signaling pathways.
